params.name: query
params.description:
Object containing query parameters as key/value pairs. Supported value types are:
  - array (will append duplicate parameter names with separate values)
  - object (will be converted to JSON)
  - boolean (will be converted to 0/1)
  - string
  - number

return.description: Complete query string with URI encoded values and prepended with a question mark (?).

content:
# OTRS JavaScript API Documentation

OTRS provides a JavaScript API to support its front end applications. It is based on ECMAScript 6 (ES6) standard and
relies on a built-in build toolchain in order to be transpiled to the code that web browsers can understand.

You can find specific module documentation in the left sidebar.

## Module Namespace

Modules can be shared or application specific, which is determined by their namespace:

* `Frontend/Apps/**/*` contains application specific code.
* `Frontend/**/*` contains shared code.

## API Families

Some JS modules can belong to an API family, which general descriptions you can find below.

* _Helpers_ contain utility methods which can be called from front end components and other JS code.
* _Mixins_ are like base classes for Vue.js components.
* _Plugins_ provide standard interfaces to Vue.js components.

## Unit Tests

JS modules are covered with unit tests based on the Jest framework. You can find them in __Frontend/Tests__ folder and
run them with `npm run unit` command.

## Code Style

All code conforms to the [Airbnb JavaScript Style Guide](https://github.com/airbnb/javascript) and
[Vue.js Style Guide](https://vuejs.org/v2/style-guide/). You can find corresponding ESLint rule definitions in the
`Frontend/.eslintrc.js` file.
